5 Subject: Motor vehicles; exhaust; exhaust system modification; emissions
6 Statement of purpose of bill as introduced: This bill proposes to prohibit the
7 installation of equipment in a motor vehicle that enhances the vehicle’s ability
8 to emit soot or smoke and to prohibit certain motor vehicles from emitting
9 excessive soot or smoke.
10 An act relating to prohibiting the emission of excessive soot or smoke from
11 certain motor vehicles
12 It is hereby enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Vermont:
13 Sec. 1. 10 V.S.A. § 567 is amended to read:
14 § 567. MOTOR VEHICLE POLLUTION
15 * * *
16 (b)(1) Except as permitted or authorized by law, no person shall fail to
17 maintain in good working order or remove, dismantle, or otherwise cause to be
18 inoperative any equipment or feature constituting an operational element of the
19 air pollution control system or mechanism of a motor vehicle and required by
20 rules pursuant to this chapter to be maintained in or on the vehicle. Any failure
